h M*T. These processes, which presumably\ncombine in situ SF in the bulge and inward migration of material from the disk,\nare expected to lead to a non-homologous radial growth of S* and a trend for an\nincreasing Sersic index with increasing galaxy mass.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 14 Dec 2017 17:32:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-12-15"}
