{"id":"1801.07748","submitter":"Sylvio Bistafa R","authors":"Sylvio R. Bistafa","title":"Attempt at a theory of the friction of fluids","comments":"The original manuscript and this translation is also available at\n  http://eulerarchive.maa.org/ , in Portuguese","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"physics.hist-ph physics.flu-dyn","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  This is a translation from Latin to Portuguese of Euler's 'Attempt at a\ntheory of the friction of fluids'. According to the records, a treatise by\nEuler with the title 'Tentamen theoriae de frictione fluidorum' was presented\nto the St. Petersburg Academy on June 17, 1754, and perhaps was read to the\nBerlin Academy on December 2, 1751. In this treatise, Euler assumes that as for\nthe solid friction, the fluid friction is proportional to the applied normal\nforce. A detailed development of five different problems of discharge are\npresented in his treatise, taking into account the loss of head in the\nconduits. In the appendix, an example is given for the calculation of the jet\nheights of a particular fountain, fed with conduits of different amplitudes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 14 Dec 2017 16:38:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-01-25"}
